(42, 18, 19, 42, 1, 35, 35, 'none is good, save one, that is, God', 'Connection of Goodness and Holiness', 'This connection highlights the nature of goodness and holiness in relation to God. In Luke 18:19, Jesus emphasizes that only God is truly good, while in Luke 1:35, the Holy Spirit''s action results in the birth of the ''holy thing,'' linking divine goodness to the identity of Jesus as the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
