(42, 18, 20, 45, 13, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the commandments, specifically mentioning ''Thou shalt not commit adultery,'' ''Thou shalt not kill,'' ''Thou shalt not steal,'' and ''Thou shalt not bear false witness.'' This connection highlights the continuity of moral teachings in the context of loving one''s neighbor.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 20, 40, 19, 17, 19, 'Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Honour thy father and thy mother', 'Connection of Commandments in Gospels', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping the commandments, listing similar prohibitions and duties. The repetition of commandments in both texts highlights their significance in moral teaching.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 20, 49, 6, 2, 2, 'Honour thy father and thy mother', 'Connection of Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of honoring parents. Luke 18:20 lists this commandment, while Ephesians 6:2 highlights it as significant with a promise.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 20, 23, 8, 20, 20, 'the commandments', 'Connection of Law and Commandments', 'This connection highlights the importance of adhering to God''s commandments as seen in both passages. Luke lists specific commandments, while Isaiah emphasizes the necessity of aligning with the law and testimony.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 20, 41, 10, 18, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Commandments in Gospels', 'Both passages emphasize the same commandments, highlighting their importance in moral teaching. The slight variation in wording, such as ''Defraud not'' in Mark, shows a shared focus on ethical behavior.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 21, 50, 3, 6, 6, NULL, 'Righteousness and Law Observance', 'Both passages emphasize adherence to the law and personal righteousness. The speaker in Luke claims to have kept the commandments, while Philippians highlights being blameless concerning the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 21, 40, 19, 20, 21, 'All these have I kept from my youth up', 'Connection of Young Man''s Response', 'Both passages emphasize the young man''s claim of having kept the commandments from his youth. This connection highlights his desire for further spiritual fulfillment and Jesus'' challenge to him.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 21, 41, 10, 20, 21, 'from my youth', 'Connection of Youthful Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the individual''s claim of having kept the commandments from youth. This connection highlights the theme of adherence to the law and the challenge presented by Jesus regarding true discipleship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 21, 42, 15, 7, 7, NULL, 'Joy in Repentance and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the contrast between those who believe they are righteous, as seen in the SOURCE verse, and the joy in heaven over a sinner''s repentance in the TARGET passage. Both passages emphasize the value of repentance and the joy it brings, suggesting that self-perceived righteousness may overlook the need for humility and repentance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
